Chess legend Bobby Fischer, facing prison in the US, seeks Icelandic citizenship to avoid deportation from Japan.
Held since July for invalid passport use, he can't renounce US citizenship.
Despite engagement to Japan Chess Association head, media overlooks his plight.
Iceland's parliament grants him citizenship, potentially preventing US return.
Fischer, critical of the US, wants Icelandic nationality.
Lawmakers support his citizenship, awaiting Japan's confirmation.
Supporters anticipate his release and plan for his new life in Iceland, where he is hailed as a hero.
Icelandic citizenship offers Fischer hope for freedom from Japanese detention and US charges.
